description:
Check out the legendary ballad of 'Ballad Of The Witches Road' from Marvel Television’s Agatha All Along.

In Marvel Studios’ “Agatha All Along,” the infamous Agatha Harkness finds herself down and out of power after a suspicious goth Teen helps break her free from a distorted spell. Her interest is piqued when he begs her to take him on the legendary Witches’ Road, a magical gauntlet of trials that, if survived, rewards a witch with what they’re missing. Together, Agatha and this mysterious Teen pull together a desperate coven, and set off down, down, down The Road…

Marvel Television’s Agatha All Along episode 5 is streaming on October 9 on ‪Disney+.

description:
Starfield: Shattered Space reviewed on PC by Dan Stapleton. Also available on Xbox Series X/S.
Starfield: Shattered Space fills the conspicuous Va’ruun-shaped hole in the main campaign with a generous helping of quest content that’s thick with snake-worshiping lore and tough, teleporting enemies. Elder Scrolls and Fallout fans will recognize a lot of these story outlines, but the Starfield twist makes them more than simple reheats. Refreshingly, the new planet is more of a traditional Bethesda-style open world that feels more like a real place where there’s a lot to do, which is a welcome improvement over hopping between mostly barren worlds. However, there’s not much to take with you once you leave, since outside of new quests and a handful of new weapons and building options there are no new gameplay systems – or even new powers or skills – you’ll want to try out after a new run through the Unity.
